frameDefinitions: An Event continues at a certain Place through Time.
An Object with an understood function is or is not in a state ready to perform that function.
An Agent initiates the beginning of an ongoing Activity in which he will be continuously involved. '' 'At the same time, city-states began to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.'
An Experiencer is involved in a bodily injury to a Body_part.
A Process stops at a certain Time and Place.
An Event begins at a certain Time and Place.
frameExamples: Pyongyang agreed to suspend its withdrawal while talks <t>continued</t> with Washington.
At the same time, city-states <t>began</t> to grow in influence on the southern Greek mainland.
I think that I <t>hurt</t> myself pretty bad back there.
listRoleDefinitions: Name of the <fen>Event</fen> which is continuing.
The entity with an understood purpose.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that an <fen>Agent</fen> starts.
This role identifies the being that starts the intentional <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> starts an <fen>Activity</fen>.
The location on the body of the <fen>Experiencer</fen> where the bodily injury takes place.
The being or entity that is injured.
The time when the harming event occurs.
The place where the harming event occurs.
listRoleExamples: I cut <fex>my finger</fex> on the envelope.
<fex>The squirrel</fex> abraded <fex>its</fex> tail as it twitched nervously in the confined space.
So you cut your leg on the window frame <fex>at six o'clock</fex>, correct?
She fell and hit her head <fex>out in the playground</fex>.
